(*
-> rrel_example:
[A camera obscura is the simplest type of device that allows you to obtain an optical image of objects.

It is a lightproof box with a hole in one of the walls and a screen (frosted glass or thin white paper) on the opposite wall.
Rays of light, passing through a small hole (the diameter of which depends on the "focal length" of the camera, approximately 0.1-5 mm), create an inverted image on the screen.]
(* <- lang_en;; *);;
